# BROWSER-core.md - Threads Global Rules & Shared Patterns


**Selectors:**
- Post links: `a[href*="/post/"]`
- Reply icon: `svg[aria-label="Reply"]`
- Textbox: `[role="textbox"][contenteditable="true"]`
- Post button: `div[role="button"]` with text "Post" — 🚨 MUST scope to `[role="dialog"]` (page has TWO "Post" buttons: nav opens new dialog, dialog submits)

**Wait pattern:** 🚨 **NEVER use a separate wait step** — each step adds 5-8s LLM overhead.
✅ **Embed waits at START of next evaluate:** `async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); ... }`

**NEVER:** `document.querySelectorAll('article')` (0 tags), class selectors like `span.x1lliihq...` (auto-generated, breaks).
**ALWAYS:** Start with `a[href*="/post/"]`, walk up DOM with `.parentElement`, use evaluate for extraction.

---

## S 5. Reply/Comment Flow (after popup is open)

Use for replies, comments, quotes (AFTER popup is already open).

**ONE evaluate** — wait 1.5s + type + wait 0.5s + click Post (verified 2026-02-19):

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); const dialog = document.querySelector('[role=\"dialog\"]'); if (!dialog) return { error: 'no_dialog' }; const textbox = dialog.querySelector('[role=\"textbox\"][contenteditable=\"true\"]'); if (!textbox) return { error: 'no_textbox' }; textbox.focus(); document.execCommand('insertText', false, window.__data.text); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); const buttons = Array.from(dialog.querySelectorAll('div[role=\"button\"]')); const postButton = buttons.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Post'); if (!postButton) return { typed: true, error: 'no_post_button_in_dialog' }; postButton.click(); return { typed: true, submitted: true }; }", "data": {"text": "YOUR_COMMENT_HERE"}}
ENDJSON
```

❌ NEVER use `document.querySelectorAll('div[role="button"]')` for Post — finds nav button first, opens duplicate dialog
✅ ALWAYS scope to `document.querySelector('[role="dialog"]').querySelectorAll(...)` for submit

Do NOT verify — replies/comments work reliably. Verification wastes steps and false-negatives on activity page.

---

## S 5b. Multiline Post Flow (original posts + quotes with formatting)

🚨 `execCommand('insertText')` with `\n` collapses to single line in Threads' Lexical editor. **Use clipboard paste for multiline content.**

Use for: original posts (S 8 → S 5b) and quote posts (S 6 → S 5b) that need line breaks.
For single-line replies/comments: use S 5 (execCommand is fine).

**ONE evaluate — clear + paste + submit:**

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); const dialog = document.querySelector('[role=\"dialog\"]'); if (!dialog) return { error: 'no_dialog' }; const textbox = dialog.querySelector('[role=\"textbox\"][contenteditable=\"true\"]'); if (!textbox) return { error: 'no_textbox' }; textbox.focus(); document.execCommand('selectAll'); document.execCommand('delete'); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); var text = window.__data.text; var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/html', text.replace(/\\n/g, '<br>')); dt.setData('text/plain', text); textbox.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); const buttons = Array.from(dialog.querySelectorAll('div[role=\"button\"]')); const postButton = buttons.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Post'); if (!postButton) return { typed: true, error: 'no_post_button_in_dialog' }; postButton.click(); return { typed: true, submitted: true, len: textbox.innerText.length }; }", "data": {"text": "YOUR_POST_TEXT"}}
ENDJSON
```
